## ðŸ“Œ Step 1: Create a Simple Project

mkdir MyGitProject
cd MyGitProject


### Create a file

echo "Hello, this is my Git project!" > app.txt



## ðŸ“Œ Step 2: Initialize Git
git init
git status




## ðŸ“Œ Step 3: Add File to Staging Area

git add app.txt


## ðŸ“Œ Step 4: Commit the File

git commit -m "Initial commit with app.txt"


## ðŸ“Œ Step 5: Create a New Branch

git branch feature-update
git checkout feature-update



## ðŸ“Œ Step 6: Modify the File

echo "Adding a new feature to the project." >> app.txt


Add + commit
git add app.txt
git commit -m "Updated app.txt with new feature"

## ðŸ“Œ Step 7: Add Remote Repository (GitHub)
ðŸ‘‰ First create a **new empty GitHub repo** (without README).

Then connect it:

git remote add origin https://github.com/<your-username>/MyGitProject.git


## ðŸ“Œ Step 8: Push Branch to GitHub

git push origin feature-update

Merge feature-update into main (from GitHub Pull Request UI)



## ðŸ“Œ Step 9: Switch to main and Pull Updated Code

git checkout main
git pull origin main




## ðŸ“Œ Step 10: Show Chronological Commit History

git log --oneline --graph --decorate --all


